description: A modification of fledge (“to acquire feathers”) due to the influence of fletcher (“arrow-maker”). Compare flèche.

entries.meaning: (archery) The vane toward the back of an arrow, used to stabilise the arrow during flight.
(fisheries) A large boneless fillet of halibut, swordfish or tuna.

verbs.description: fletch (third-person singular simple present fletches, present participle fletching, simple past and past participle fletched)
